# React Shopping App

## Description

This project demonstrates the use of React Props by passing shopping cart data from the OnlineShopping component to the Cart component and displaying the items in a table.

## Technologies Used

- React
- JavaScript (ES6)
- HTML
- CSS
- Node.js
- npm

## Features

- React Class Components
- Props
- Parent to Child Communication
- Dynamic Table Rendering
- Shopping Cart Display

## Project Structure

```
shoppingapp
│
├── src
│   ├── Components
│   │   ├── OnlineShopping.js
│   │   └── Cart.js
│   ├── App.js
│   └── index.js
```

## Installation

```bash
git clone https://github.com/your-username/shoppingapp.git
cd shoppingapp
npm install
npm start
```

## Output

Displays a shopping cart containing items such as:

- TV
- Fridge
- Washing Machine
- Mobile
- Table

Each item is displayed with its corresponding price in a table.

## Learning Outcomes

- React Props
- Parent to Child Data Passing
- Component Reusability
- Rendering Lists using map()
- Class Components
